Key Match Events: Robbie Brady scored the winning goal in the 88th minute with a powerful header from a cross by Ebosele
Finland took the lead in the 17th minute with Pohjanpalo scoring a low hard effort past Kelleher
Ireland equalized in the 57th minute with Liam Scales heading in a cross from Brady
Ireland secured their first away win in the UEFA Nations League campaign
Post-Match Reflections: Robbie Brady was named Player of the Match
This was the first time since 2011 that Ireland has come from behind to win away from home
